<subSubSection id="C34E6519FFB2FFEDC5FAFD7DFE71FC5F" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEB3692FFB2FFEDC5FAFD7DFE71FC5F" blockId="11.[151,1436,762,1219]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis id="B920EA80FFB2FFEDC5FAFD7DFEA3FCEE" bold="true" box="[151,273,762,787]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. In the group IV key of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC54B63FFB2FFEDC7FBFD7DFCDAFCEE" author="Borgmeier" box="[662,872,762,787]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refString="Borgmeier, T. (1964) Revision of the North American phorid flies. Part II. The species of the genus Megaselia, subgenus Aphiochaeta. Studia Entomologica, 7, 257 - 416." type="journal article" year="1964">
Borgmeier (
<number id="3D9C24B5FFB2FFEDC64EFD7DFCEDFCEE" box="[803,863,762,787]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, keys to 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D11FFB2FFEDC6B3FD7CFB20FCEF" authority="Brues" authorityName="Brues" box="[990,1170,763,787]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulla">
<emphasis id="B920EA80FFB2FFEDC6B3FD7CFBF6FCEE" box="[990,1092,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">M. pulla</emphasis>
Brues
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs substantially in the structure of the genitalia (
<figureCitation id="136F2A17FFB2FFEDC7FBFC99FD59FCCA" box="[662,747,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 80" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1740,1763]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,186,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[150,1436,169,1732]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 80. Male genitalia, left lateral. 75. Megaselia hentschkeae. 76. Megaselia hoffmanorum. 77. Megaselia hoggorum. 78. Megaselia hoguei. 79. Megaselia isaacmajorum. 80. Megaselia kelleri" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242986/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9C24B5FFB2FFEDC7A6FC99FD59FCCA" box="[715,747,798,823]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="76.0">76</number>
</figureCitation>
). Whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D11FFB2FFEDC604FC98FC7BFCCB" box="[873,969,798,822]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulla">
<emphasis id="B920EA80FFB2FFEDC604FC98FC7BFCCB" box="[873,969,798,822]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">M. pulla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an oblique ascending row of delicate bristles on the left side of the epandrium and 
<number id="3D9C24B5FFB2FFEDC7FFFCC4FD12FCA6" box="[658,672,835,859]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="4.0">4</number>
marginal bristles on the right, 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D11FFB2FFEDC695FCC4FB06FCA6" box="[1016,1204,835,859]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoffmanorum">
<emphasis id="B920EA80FFB2FFEDC695FCC4FB06FCA6" box="[1016,1204,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">M. hoffmanorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a nearly vertical arrangement of strong hairs on either side. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D11FFB2FFEDC678FCE0FC60FC83" box="[789,978,870,894]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoffmanorum">
<emphasis id="B920EA80FFB2FFEDC678FCE0FC60FC83" box="[789,978,870,894]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">M. hoffmanorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the moderate bristles described on the epandrium of 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D11FFB2FFEDC430FC0CFE0EFC5E" box="[349,444,907,931]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulla">
<emphasis id="B920EA80FFB2FFEDC430FC0CFE0EFC5E" box="[349,444,907,931]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">M. pulla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
